    "Jdg 18:23": "And they cried unto the children H1121 of Dan. And they turned their faces, and said unto Micah, What aileth thee, that thou comest with such a company?",
    "Jdg 18:25": "And the children H1121 of Dan said unto him, Let not thy voice be heard among us, lest angry fellows run upon thee, and thou lose thy life, with the lives of thy household.",
    "Jdg 18:26": "And the children H1121 of Dan went their way: and when Micah saw that they were too strong for him, he turned and went back unto his house.",
    "Jdg 18:30": "And the children H1121 of Dan set up the graven image: and Jonathan, the son H1121 of Gershom, the son H1121 of Manasseh, he and his sons H1121 were priests to the tribe of Dan until the day of the captivity of the land.",
    "Jdg 19:12": "And his master said unto him, We will not turn aside hither into the city of a stranger, that is not of the children H1121 of Israel; we will pass over to Gibeah.",
    "Jdg 19:22": "Now as they were making their hearts merry, behold, the men of the city, certain sons H1121 of Belial, beset the house round about, and beat at the door, and spake to the master of the house, the old man, saying, Bring forth the man that came into thine house, that we may know him.",
    "Jdg 19:30": "And it was so, that all that saw it said, There was no such deed done nor seen from the day that the children H1121 of Israel came up out of the land of Egypt unto this day: consider of it, take advice, and speak your minds.",
    "Jdg 20:1": "Then all the children H1121 of Israel went out, and the congregation was gathered together as one man, from Dan even to Beersheba, with the land of Gilead, unto the LORD in Mizpeh.",
    "Jdg 20:3": "(Now the children H1121 of Benjamin heard that the children H1121 of Israel were gone up to Mizpeh.) Then said the children H1121 of Israel, Tell us, how was this wickedness?",
    "Jdg 20:7": "Behold, ye are all children H1121 of Israel; give here your advice and counsel.",
    "Jdg 20:13": "Now therefore deliver us the men, the children H1121 of Belial, which are in Gibeah, that we may put them to death, and put away evil from Israel. But the children H1121 of Benjamin would not hearken to the voice of their brethren the children H1121 of Israel:",
    "Jdg 20:14": "But the children H1121 of Benjamin gathered themselves together out of the cities unto Gibeah, to go out to battle against the children H1121 of Israel.",
    "Jdg 20:15": "And the children H1121 of Benjamin were numbered at that time out of the cities twenty and six thousand men that drew sword, beside the inhabitants of Gibeah, which were numbered seven hundred chosen men.",
