    "Ezr 2:55": "The children H1121 of Solomon's servants: the children H1121 of Sotai, the children H1121 of Sophereth, the children H1121 of Peruda,",
    "Ezr 2:56": "The children H1121 of Jaalah, the children H1121 of Darkon, the children H1121 of Giddel,",
    "Ezr 2:57": "The children H1121 of Shephatiah, the children H1121 of Hattil, the children H1121 of Pochereth of Zebaim, the children H1121 of Ami.",
    "Ezr 2:58": "All the Nethinims, and the children H1121 of Solomon's servants, were three hundred ninety and two.",
    "Ezr 2:60": "The children H1121 of Delaiah, the children H1121 of Tobiah, the children H1121 of Nekoda, six hundred fifty and two.",
    "Ezr 2:61": "And of the children H1121 of the priests: the children H1121 of Habaiah, the children H1121 of Koz, the children H1121 of Barzillai; which took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and was called after their name:",
    "Ezr 3:1": "And when the seventh month was come, and the children H1121 of Israel were in the cities, the people gathered themselves together as one man to Jerusalem.",
    "Ezr 3:2": "Then stood up Jeshua the son H1121 of Jozadak, and his brethren the priests, and Zerubbabel the son H1121 of Shealtiel, and his brethren, and builded the altar of the God of Israel, to offer burnt offerings thereon, as it is written in the law of Moses the man of God.",
    "Ezr 3:8": "Now in the second year of their coming unto the house of God at Jerusalem, in the second month, began Zerubbabel the son H1121 of Shealtiel, and Jeshua the son H1121 of Jozadak, and the remnant of their brethren the priests and the Levites, and all they that were come out of the captivity unto Jerusalem; and appointed the Levites, from twenty years old H1121 and upward, to set forward the work of the house of the LORD.",
    "Ezr 3:9": "Then stood Jeshua with his sons H1121 and his brethren, Kadmiel and his sons, H1121 the sons H1121 of Judah, together, to set forward the workmen in the house of God: the sons H1121 of Henadad, with their sons H1121 and their brethren the Levites.",
    "Ezr 3:10": "And when the builders laid the foundation of the temple of the LORD, they set the priests in their apparel with trumpets, and the Levites the sons H1121 of Asaph with cymbals, to praise the LORD, after the ordinance of David king of Israel.",
    "Ezr 4:1": "Now when the adversaries of Judah and Benjamin heard that the children H1121 of the captivity builded the temple unto the LORD God of Israel;",
    "Ezr 6:19": "And the children H1121 of the captivity kept the passover upon the fourteenth day of the first month.",
    "Ezr 6:20": "For the priests and the Levites were purified together, all of them were pure, and killed the passover for all the children H1121 of the captivity, and for their brethren the priests, and for themselves.",
    "Ezr 6:21": "And the children H1121 of Israel, which were come again out of captivity, and all such as had separated themselves unto them from the filthiness of the heathen of the land, to seek the LORD God of Israel, did eat,",
    "Ezr 7:1": "Now after these things, in the reign of Artaxerxes king of Persia, Ezra the son H1121 of Seraiah, the son H1121 of Azariah, the son H1121 of Hilkiah,",
    "Ezr 7:2": "The son H1121 of Shallum, the son H1121 of Zadok, the son H1121 of Ahitub,",
    "Ezr 7:3": "The son H1121 of Amariah, the son H1121 of Azariah, the son H1121 of Meraioth,",
    "Ezr 7:4": "The son H1121 of Zerahiah, the son H1121 of Uzzi, the son H1121 of Bukki,",
    "Ezr 7:5": "The son H1121 of Abishua, the son H1121 of Phinehas, the son H1121 of Eleazar, the son H1121 of Aaron the chief priest:",
    "Ezr 7:7": "And there went up some of the children H1121 of Israel, and of the priests, and the Levites, and the singers, and the porters, and the Nethinims, unto Jerusalem, in the seventh year of Artaxerxes the king.",
    "Ezr 8:2": "Of the sons H1121 of Phinehas; Gershom: of the sons H1121 of Ithamar; Daniel: of the sons H1121 of David; Hattush.",
    "Ezr 8:3": "Of the sons H1121 of Shechaniah, of the sons H1121 of Pharosh; Zechariah: and with him were reckoned by genealogy of the males an hundred and fifty.",
    "Ezr 8:4": "Of the sons H1121 of Pahathmoab; Elihoenai the son H1121 of Zerahiah, and with him two hundred males.",
    "Ezr 8:5": "Of the sons H1121 of Shechaniah; the son H1121 of Jahaziel, and with him three hundred males.",
    "Ezr 8:6": "Of the sons H1121 also of Adin; Ebed the son H1121 of Jonathan, and with him fifty males.",
    "Ezr 8:7": "And of the sons H1121 of Elam; Jeshaiah the son H1121 of Athaliah, and with him seventy males.",
    "Ezr 8:8": "And of the sons H1121 of Shephatiah; Zebadiah the son H1121 of Michael, and with him fourscore males.",
    "Ezr 8:9": "Of the sons H1121 of Joab; Obadiah the son H1121 of Jehiel, and with him two hundred and eighteen males.",
    "Ezr 8:10": "And of the sons H1121 of Shelomith; the son H1121 of Josiphiah, and with him an hundred and threescore males.",
    "Ezr 8:11": "And of the sons H1121 of Bebai; Zechariah the son H1121 of Bebai, and with him twenty and eight males.",
    "Ezr 8:12": "And of the sons H1121 of Azgad; Johanan the son H1121 of Hakkatan, and with him an hundred and ten males.",
    "Ezr 8:13": "And of the last sons H1121 of Adonikam, whose names are these, Eliphelet, Jeiel, and Shemaiah, and with them threescore males.",
    "Ezr 8:14": "Of the sons H1121 also of Bigvai; Uthai, and Zabbud, and with them seventy males.",
    "Ezr 8:15": "And I gathered them together to the river that runneth to Ahava; and there abode we in tents three days: and I viewed the people, and the priests, and found there none of the sons H1121 of Levi.",
    "Ezr 8:18": "And by the good hand of our God upon us they brought us a man of understanding, of the sons H1121 of Mahli, the son H1121 of Levi, the son H1121 of Israel; and Sherebiah, with his sons H1121 and his brethren, eighteen;",
    "Ezr 8:19": "And Hashabiah, and with him Jeshaiah of the sons H1121 of Merari, his brethren and their sons, H1121 twenty;",
    "Ezr 8:33": "Now on the fourth day was the silver and the gold and the vessels weighed in the house of our God by the hand of Meremoth the son H1121 of Uriah the priest; and with him was Eleazar the son H1121 of Phinehas; and with them was Jozabad the son H1121 of Jeshua, and Noadiah the son H1121 of Binnui, Levites;",
    "Ezr 8:35": "Also the children H1121 of those that had been carried away, which were come out of the captivity, offered burnt offerings unto the God of Israel, twelve bullocks for all Israel, ninety and six rams, seventy and seven lambs, twelve he goats for a sin offering: all this was a burnt offering unto the LORD.",
    "Ezr 9:2": "For they have taken of their daughters for themselves, and for their sons: H1121 so that the holy seed have mingled themselves with the people of those lands: yea, the hand of the princes and rulers hath been chief in this trespass.",
    "Ezr 9:12": "Now therefore give not your daughters unto their sons, H1121 neither take their daughters unto your sons, H1121 nor seek their peace or their wealth for ever: that ye may be strong, and eat the good of the land, and leave it for an inheritance to your children H1121 for ever.",
    "Ezr 10:2": "And Shechaniah the son H1121 of Jehiel, one of the sons H1121 of Elam, answered and said unto Ezra, We have trespassed against our God, and have taken strange wives of the people of the land: yet now there is hope in Israel concerning this thing.",
    "Ezr 10:6": "Then Ezra rose up from before the house of God, and went into the chamber of Johanan the son H1121 of Eliashib: and when he came thither, he did eat no bread, nor drink water: for he mourned because of the transgression of them that had been carried away.",
    "Ezr 10:7": "And they made proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem unto all the children H1121 of the captivity, that they should gather themselves together unto Jerusalem;",
