    "Neh 1:1": "The words of Nehemiah the son H1121 of Hachaliah. And it came to pass in the month Chisleu, in the twentieth year, as I was in Shushan the palace,",
    "Neh 1:6": "Let thine ear now be attentive, and thine eyes open, that thou mayest hear the prayer of thy servant, which I pray before thee now, day and night, for the children H1121 of Israel thy servants, and confess the sins of the children H1121 of Israel, which we have sinned against thee: both I and my father's house have sinned.",
    "Neh 2:10": "When Sanballat the Horonite, and Tobiah the servant, the Ammonite, heard of it, it grieved them exceedingly that there was come a man to seek the welfare of the children H1121 of Israel.",
