    "Neh 3:31": "After him repaired Malchiah the goldsmith's son H1121 unto the place of the Nethinims, and of the merchants, over against the gate Miphkad, and to the going up of the corner.",
    "Neh 4:14": "And I looked, and rose up, and said unto the nobles, and to the rulers, and to the rest of the people, Be not ye afraid of them: remember the Lord, which is great and terrible, and fight for your brethren, your sons, H1121 and your daughters, your wives, and your houses.",
    "Neh 5:2": "For there were that said, We, our sons, H1121 and our daughters, are many: therefore we take up corn for them, that we may eat, and live.",
